 A Chinese mother has bought a $6.5 million (£4.3 million) flat in Manhattan for her toddler.

The woman told the New York based real estate agency that she wants the flat for when her daughter leaves home for college.

Kevin Brown, a senior vice president at Sotheby's International who specialises in selling the city's prestigious property, said the unnamed woman had snapped up the flat, CCTV reported..

